pokedexEntries.red: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.
pokedexEntries.blue: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Its entire body is a snowy-white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.
pokedexEntries.gold: Its streamlined body has little drag in water. The colder the temperature, the friskier it gets.
pokedexEntries.silver: It loves frigid seas with ice floes. It uses its long tail to change swimming direction quickly.
pokedexEntries.crystal: It sleeps under shallow ocean waters during the day, then looks for food at night when it's cold.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Dewgong loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this Pokémon sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Dewgong loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this Pokémon sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.
pokedexEntries.emerald: It loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this Pokémon sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: Its body is covered with a pure white fur. The colder the weather, the more active it becomes.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: It stores thermal energy in the body. It swims at a steady eight knots even in intensely cold waters.
pokedexEntries.diamond: In snow, the pure white coat covering its body obscures it from predators.

pokedexEntries.black2: Its streamlined body has low resistance, and it swims around cold oceans at a speed of eight knots.

pokedexEntries.ultraSun: It swims through the ocean at a speed of eight knots, searching for Pokémon that will become its prey. It’s especially fond of Wishiwashi.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.
